Installing Ruby on Rails on Ubuntu:

sudo apt-get update

sudo apt install curl

gpg --keyserver hkp://keys.gnupg.net --recv-keys 409B6B1796C275462A1703113804BB82D39DC0E3 7D2BAF1CF37B13E2069D6956105BD0E739499BDB

\curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable

source ~/.rvm/scripts/rvm

rvm requirements

rvm install 2.6.3

rvm use ruby --default

rvm rubygems current

gem install rails

 
IMPORTANT --> TO RUN RUBY FROM ANY TERMINAL SESSION WE HAVE TO DO THE SETTINGS CHANGE=>
	Terminal->(Top Menu)Edit->Preferences->Command->Run As LOgin Shell

*******************
We must install Nodejs for runtime Environmnt(else it will give runtime error)
sudo apt install nodejs

Initiating a Rails project:

rails new proj

cd proj

bundle install

rails server


